Gather Data:

	1) CPU Utilization every minute (note: Global average only, not per-core)
		a. CPU Utilization
	2) Memory every 5 minutes (note: Global average only, not per-NUMA-node)
		a. Buffer Cache Hit Ratio
		b. Page Life Expectancy
	3) Disk Latency (note: data per file: mdf, ndf, log)
		a. Read/Write/Average Latency
		b. Bytes per Read/Write/Transfer
		c. Disk, DatabaseName, filenames (+path)
	4) Blocking (note: gather daily and delete previous data since the last server restart)
		a. Basic cumulative blocking per DB object
		b. Analysis? Add cumulative times between restarts at check period
		c. Analysis? Perhaps both expression of absolute time and relative % of processing time?
	5) Deadlocks?
